						<summary>

						<p>The king might possibly be Jaṭāvarman Parākrama I of acc. A.D. 1315. The inscription records a gift of 120 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> left with three temple servants for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Naḍuviṟkōyil-Perumāḷ at Arikēsarinallūr by a certain Mōchcharāmaṉ Aṉantanārāyaṇaṉ of Tirupputtūr.</p>						

						</summary>
